obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (49833)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 13 of 2021, s. 172 (w.e.f. 17-03-2020).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00039_202003_1584597766943&sectionId=49833&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00039_202003_1584597766943
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `(1) In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,---`
  line
  line `'(a) "appellant" means---`
  line
  line `(i) a person in whose case an appeal or a writ petition or special leave petition has been filed`
  line `either by him or by the income-tax authority or by both, before an appellate forum and such`
  line `appeal or petition is pending as on the specified date;`
  line
  line `(ii) a person in whose case an order has been passed by the Assessing Officer, or an order has`
  line `been passed by the Commissioner (Appeals) or the Income Tax Appellate Tribunal in an appeal,`
  line `or by the High Court in a writ petition, on or before the specified date, and the time for filing any`
  line `appeal or special leave petition against such order by that person has not expired as on that date;`
  line
  line `(iii) a person who has filed his objections before the Dispute Resolution Panel under section`
  line `144C of the Income-tax Act, 1961 (43 of 1961) and the Dispute Resolution Panel has not issued`
  line `any direction on or before the specified date;`
  line
  line `(iv) a person in whose case the Dispute Resolution Panel has issued direction under`
  line `sub-section (5) of section 144C of the Income-tax Act and the Assessing Officer has not passed`
  line `any order under sub-section (13) of that section on or before the specified date;`
  line
  line `(v) a person who has filed an application for revision under section 264 of the Income-tax Act`
  line `and such application is pending as on the specified date;";`
  line
  line `^1[Explanation.---For the removal of doubts, it is hereby clarified that the expression`
  line `appellant shall not include and shall be deemed never to have been included a person in whose`
  line `case a writ petition or special leave petition or any other proceeding has been filed either by him`
  line `or by the income-tax authority or by both before an appellate forum, arising out of an order of the`
  line `Settlement Commission under Chapter XIX-A of the Income-tax Act, and such petition or appeal`
  line `is either pending or is disposed of.]`
  line
  line `(b) "appellate forum" means the Supreme Court or the High Court or the Income Tax Appellate`
  line `Tribunal or the Commissioner (Appeals);`
  line
  line `(c) "declarant" means a person who files declaration under section 4;`
  line
  line `(d) "declaration" means the declaration filed under section 4;`
  line
  line `(e) "designated authority" means an officer not below the rank of a Commissioner of Income-tax`
  line `notified by the Principal Chief Commissioner for the purposes of this Act;`
  line
  line `(f) "disputed fee" means the fee determined under the provisions of the Income-tax Act, 1961`
  line `(43 of 1961) in respect of which appeal has been filed by the appellant;`
  line
  line `(g) "disputed income", in relation to an assessment year, means the whole or so much of the total`
  line `income as is relatable to the disputed tax;`
  line
  line `(h) "disputed interest" means the interest determined in any case under the provisions of the`
  line `Income-tax Act, 1961 (43 of 1961), where--`
  line
  line `(i) such interest is not charged or chargeable on disputed tax;`
  line
  line `(ii) an appeal has been filed by the appellant in respect of such interest;`
  line
  line `(i) "disputed penalty" means the penalty determined in any case under the provisions of the`
  line `Income-tax Act, 1961 (43 of 1961), where---`
  line
  line `(i) such penalty is not levied or leviable in respect of disputed income or disputed tax, as the`
  line `case may be;`
  line
  line `(ii) an appeal has been filed by the appellant in respect of such penalty;`
  line
  line `(j) "disputed tax", in relation to an assessment year or financial year, as the case may be, means`
  line `the income-tax, including surcharge and cess (hereafter in this clause referred to as the amount of tax)`
  line `payable by the appellant under the provisions of the Income-tax Act, 1961 (43 of 1961), as computed`
  line `hereunder:---`
  line
  line `(A) in a case where any appeal, writ petition or special leave petition is pending before the`
  line `appellate forum as on the specified date, the amount of tax that is payable by the appellant if such`
  line `appeal or writ petition or special leave petition was to be decided against him;`
  line
  line `(B) in a case where an order in an appeal or in writ petition has been passed by the appellate`
  line `forum on or before the specified date, and the time for filing appeal or special leave petition`
  line `against such order has not expired as on that date, the amount of tax payable by the appellant after`
  line `giving effect to the order so passed;`
  line
  line `(C) in a case where the order has been passed by the Assessing Officer on or before the`
  line `specified date, and the time for filing appeal against such order has not expired as on that date, the`
  line `amount of tax payable by the appellant in accordance with such order;`
  line
  line `(D) in a case where objection filed by the appellant is pending before the Dispute Resolution`
  line `Panel under section 144C of the Income-tax Act as on the specified date, the amount of tax`
  line `payable by the appellant if the Dispute Resolution Panel was to confirm the variation proposed in`
  line `the draft order;`
  line
  line `(E) in a case where Dispute Resolution Panel has issued any direction under sub-section (5)`
  line `of section 144C of the Income-tax Act and the Assessing Officer has not passed the order under`
  line `sub-section (13) of that section on or before the specified date, the amount of tax payable by the`
  line `appellant as per the assessment order to be passed by the Assessing Officer under sub-section`
  line `(13) thereof;`
  line
  line `(F) in a case where an application for revision under section 264 of the Income-tax Act is`
  line `pending as on the specified date, the amount of tax payable by the appellant if such application`
  line `for revision was not to be accepted:`
  line
  line `Provided that in a case where Commissioner (Appeals) has issued notice of enhancement`
  line `under section 251 of the Income-tax Act on or before the specified date, the disputed tax shall be`
  line `increased by the amount of tax pertaining to issues for which notice of enhancement has been`
  line `issued:`
  line
  line `Provided further that in a case where the dispute in relation to an assessment year relates to`
  line `reduction of tax credit under section 115JAA or section 115JD of the Income-tax Act or any loss`
  line `or depreciation computed thereunder, the appellant shall have an option either to include the amount of tax related to such tax credit or loss or depreciation in the amount of disputed tax, or to`
  line `carry forward the reduced tax credit or loss or depreciation, in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `^1[Explanation.---For the removal of doubts, it is hereby clarified that the expression`
  line `"disputed tax", in relation to an assessment year or financial year, as the case may be, shall not`
  line `include and shall be deemed never to have been included any sum payable either by way of tax,`
  line `penalty or interest pursuant to an order passed by the Settlement Commission under Chapter XIX-A of the Income-tax Act.]`
  line
  line `(k) "Income-tax Act" means the Income-tax Act, 1961 (43 of 1961);`
  line
  line `(l) "last date" means such date as may be notified by the Central Government in the Official`
  line Gazette;
  line
  line `(m) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(n) "specified date" means the 31st day of January, 2020;`
  line
  line `(o)" tax arrear" means,---`
  line
  line `(i) the aggregate amount of disputed tax, interest chargeable or charged on such disputed tax,`
  line `and penalty leviable or levied on such disputed tax; or`
  line
  line `(ii) disputed interest; or`
  line
  line `(iii) disputed penalty; or`
  line
  line `(iv) disputed fee,`
  line
  line `as determined under the provisions of the Income-tax Act.`
  line
  line `^1[Explanation.---For the removal of doubts, it is hereby clarified that the expression tax`
  line `arrear shall not include and shall be deemed never to have been included any sum payable either`
  line `by way of tax, penalty or interest pursuant to an order passed by the Settlement Commission`
  line `under Chapter XIX-A of the Income-tax Act.]`
  line
  line `(2) The words and expressions used herein and not defined but defined in the Income-tax Act shall`
  line `have the meanings respectively assigned to them in that Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (49834)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Amount payable by declarant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00039_202003_1584597766943&sectionId=49834&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00039_202003_1584597766943
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this Act, where a declarant files`
  line `^1[under the provisions of this Act on or before the such date^* as may be notified], a declaration to the`
  line `designated authority in accordance with the provisions of section 4 in respect of tax arrear, then,`
  line `notwithstanding anything contained in the Income-tax Act or any other law for the time being in force, the`
  line `amount payable by the declarant under this Act shall be as under, namely:--`
  line
  line SI.
  line NO
  line `Nature of tax arrear. Amount payable under`
  line `this Act on or before the`
  line `^2[31st day of December,`
  line `2020 or such later date`
  line `as may be notified].`
  line `Amount payable under this Act on or after the ^3[1st day of January, 2021 or such later date as may be notified] but on or before the last date.`
  line
  line `(a) where the tax arrear is the aggregate`
  line `amount of disputed tax, interest`
  line `chargeable or charged on such`
  line `disputed tax and penalty leviable or`
  line `levied on such disputed tax.`
  line `amount of the disputed`
  line tax.
  line `the aggregate of the`
  line `amount of disputed`
  line `tax and ten per cent.`
  line `of disputed tax:`
  line `provided that where`
  line `the ten per cent. of`
  line `disputed tax exceeds`
  line `the aggregate amount`
  line `of interest chargeable`
  line `or charged on such`
  line `disputed tax and`
  line `penalty leviable or`
  line `levied on such`
  line `disputed tax, the`
  line `excess shall be`
  line `ignored forthe`
  line `purpose of`
  line `computation of`
  line `amount payable`
  line `under this Act .`
  line
  line `(b)`
  line `where the tax arrear includes the`
  line `tax, interest or penalty determined`
  line `in any assessment on the basis of`
  line `search under section 132 or section`
  line `132A of the Income-tax Act.`
  line `the aggregate of the`
  line `amount of disputed`
  line `tax and twenty-five`
  line `per cent. of the`
  line `disputed tax:`
  line
  line `provided that where the`
  line `twenty-five per cent. of`
  line `disputed tax exceeds the`
  line `aggregate amount of`
  line `interest chargeable or`
  line `charged on such`
  line `disputed tax and penalty`
  line `leviable or levied on`
  line `such disputed tax, the`
  line `excess shall be ignored`
  line `for the purpose of`
  line `computation of amount`
  line `payable under this Act.`
  line
  line `the aggregate of the`
  line `amount of disputed`
  line `tax and thirty-five per`
  line `cent. of disputed tax:`
  line
  line `provided that where`
  line `the thirty- five per`
  line `cent. of disputed tax`
  line `exceeds the aggregate`
  line `amount of interest`
  line `chargeable or charged`
  line `on such disputed`
  line `tax and penalty`
  line `leviable or levied on`
  line `such disputed tax, the`
  line `excess shall be`
  line `ignored for the`
  line `purpose of`
  line `computation of`
  line `amount payable.`
  line
  line `(c)`
  line `where the tax arrear relates to`
  line `disputed interest or disputed`
  line `penalty or disputed fee.`
  line `twenty-five per cent.`
  line `of disputed interest`
  line `or disputed penalty`
  line `or disputed fee.`
  line `thirty per cent. of`
  line `disputed interest or`
  line `disputed penalty or`
  line `disputed fee:`
  line
  line `Provided that in a case where an appeal or writ petition or special leave petition is filed by the`
  line `income-tax authority on any issue before the appellate forum, the amount payable shall be one-half of the`
  line `amount in the Table above calculated on such issue, in such manner as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided further that in a case where an appeal is filed before the Commissioner (Appeals) or`
  line `objections is filed before the Dispute Resolution Panel by the appellant on any issue on which he has`
  line `already got a decision in his favour from the Income Tax Appellate Tribunal (where the decision on such`
  line `issue is not reversed by the High Court or the Supreme Court) or the High Court (where the decision on`
  line `such issue is not reversed by the Supreme Court), the amount payable shall be one-half of the amount in`
  line `the Table above calculated on such issue, in such manner as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided also that in a case where an appeal is filed by the appellant on any issue before the Income`
  line `Tax Appellate Tribunal on which he has already got a decision in his favour from the High Court (where`
  line `the decision on such issue is not reversed by the Supreme Court), the amount payable shall be one-half of`
  line `the amount in the Table above calculated on such issue, in such manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 38 of 2020, s. 5, for "under the provisions of this Act on or before the last date" (w.e.f. 31-3-2020).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 5, ibid., for "31st day of March, 2020" (w.e.f. 31-3-2020).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 5, ibid., for "1st day of April, 2020" (w.e.f. 31-3-2020).`
  line
  line `* 28th February, 2021, vide notification No. S.O. 471(E), dated 31st January, 2021.`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (49835)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Filing of declaration and particulars to be furnished`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00039_202003_1584597766943&sectionId=49835&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00039_202003_1584597766943
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The declaration referred to in section`
  line `3 shall be filed by the declarant before the designated authority in such form and verified in such manner`
  line `as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Upon the filing the declaration, any appeal pending before the Income Tax Appellate Tribunal or`
  line `Commissioner (Appeals), in respect of the disputed income or disputed interest or disputed penalty or`
  line `disputed fee and tax arrear shall be deemed to have been withdrawn from the date on which certificate`
  line `under sub-section (1) of section 5 is issued by the designated authority.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the declarant has filed any appeal before the appellate forum or any writ petition before the`
  line `High Court or the Supreme Court against any order in respect of tax arrear, he shall withdraw such appeal`
  line `or writ petition with the leave of the Court wherever required after issuance of certificate under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 5 and furnish proof of such withdrawal alongwith the intimation of payment to`
  line `the designated authority under sub-section (2) of section 5.`
  line
  line `(4) Where the declarant has initiated any proceeding for arbitration, conciliation or mediation, or has`
  line `given any notice thereof under any law for the time being in force or under any agreement entered into by`
  line `India with any other country or territory outside India whether for protection of investment or otherwise,`
  line `he shall withdraw the claim, if any, in such proceedings or notice after issuance of certificate under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 5 and furnish proof of such withdrawal alongwith the intimation of payment to`
  line `the designated authority under sub-section (2) of section 5.`
  line
  line `(5) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-sections (2), (3) and (4), the declarant shall furnish an`
  line `undertaking waiving his right, whether direct or indirect, to seek or pursue any remedy or any claim in`
  line `relation to the tax arrear which may otherwise be available to him under any law for the time being in`
  line `force, in equity, under statute or under any agreement entered into by India with any country or territory`
  line `outside India whether for protection of investment or otherwise and the undertaking shall be made in such`
  line `form and manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(6) The declaration under sub-section (1) shall be presumed never to have been made if,--`
  line
  line `(a) any material particular furnished in the declaration is found to be false at any stage;`
  line
  line `(b) the declarant violates any of the conditions referred to in this Act;`
  line
  line `(c) the declarant acts in any manner which is not in accordance with the undertaking given by him`
  line `under sub-section (5),`
  line
  line `and in such cases, all the proceedings and claims which were withdrawn under section 4 and all the`
  line `consequences under the Income-tax Act against the declarant shall be deemed to have been revived.`
  line
  line `(7) No appellate forum or arbitrator, conciliator or mediator shall proceed to decide any issue relating`
  line `to the tax arrear mentioned in the declaration in respect of which an order has been made under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 5 by the designated authority or the payment of sum determined under that`
  line section.
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (49836)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Time and manner of payment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00039_202003_1584597766943&sectionId=49836&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00039_202003_1584597766943
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The designated authority shall, within a period of fifteen`
  line `days from the date of receipt of the declaration, by order, determine the amount payable by the declarant`
  line `in accordance with the provisions of this Act and grant a certificate to the declarant containing particulars`
  line `of the tax arrear and the amount payable after such determination, in such form as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The declarant shall pay the amount determined under sub-section (1) within fifteen days of the`
  line `date of receipt of the certificate and intimate the details of such payment to the designated authority in the`
  line `prescribed form and thereupon the designated authority shall pass an order stating that the declarant has`
  line `paid the amount.`
  line
  line `(3) Every order passed under sub-section (1), determining the amount payable under this Act, shall be`
  line `conclusive as to the matters stated therein and no matter covered by such order shall be reopened in any`
  line `other proceeding under the Income-tax Act or under any other law for the time being in force or under`
  line `any agreement, whether for protection of investment or otherwise, entered into by India with any other`
  line `country or territory outside India.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the removal of doubts, it is hereby clarified that making a declaration under this`
  line `Act shall not amount to conceding the tax position and it shall not be lawful for the income-tax authority`
  line `or the declarant being a party in appeal or writ petition or special leave petition to contend that the`
  line `declarant or the income-tax authority, as the case may be, has acquiesced in the decision on the disputed`
  line `issue by settling the dispute.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (49837)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Immunity from initiation of proceedings in respect of offence and imposition of penalty in certain cases`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00039_202003_1584597766943&sectionId=49837&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00039_202003_1584597766943
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of section 5, the designated authority shall not institute any`
  line `proceeding in respect of an offence; or impose or levy any penalty; or charge any interest under the`
  line `Income-tax Act in respect of tax arrear.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (49838)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `No refund of amount paid.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00039_202003_1584597766943&sectionId=49838&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00039_202003_1584597766943
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `Any amount paid in pursuance of a declaration made under section 4`
  line `shall not be refundable under any circumstances.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the removal of doubts, it is hereby clarified that where the declarant had, before`
  line `filing the declaration under sub-section (1) of section 4, paid any amount under the Income-tax Act in`
  line `respect of his tax arrear which exceeds the amount payable under section 3, he shall be entitled to a refund`
  line `of such excess amount, but shall not be entitled to interest on such excess amount under section 244A of`
  line `the Income-tax Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (49839)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `No benefit, concession or immunity to declarant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00039_202003_1584597766943&sectionId=49839&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00039_202003_1584597766943
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise expressly provided in`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 5 or section 6, nothing contained in this Act shall be construed as conferring`
  line `any benefit, concession or immunity on the declarant in any proceedings other than those in relation to`
  line `which the declaration has been made.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (49840)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Act not to apply in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00039_202003_1584597766943&sectionId=49840&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00039_202003_1584597766943
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall not apply--`
  line
  line `(a) in respect of tax arrear,--`
  line
  line `(i) relating to an assessment year in respect of which an assessment has been made under`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 143 or section 144 or section 153A or section 153C of the Income-tax`
  line `Act on the basis of search initiated under section 132 or section 132A of the Income-tax Act, if`
  line `the amount of disputed tax exceeds five crore rupees;`
  line
  line `(ii) relating to an assessment year in respect of which prosecution has been instituted on or`
  line `before the date of filing of declaration;`
  line
  line `(iii) relating to any undisclosed income from a source located outside India or undisclosed`
  line `asset located outside India;`
  line
  line `(iv) relating to an assessment or reassessment made on the basis of information received`
  line `under an agreement referred to in section 90 or section 90A of the Income-tax Act, if it relates to`
  line `any tax arrear;`
  line
  line `(b) to any person in respect of whom an order of detention has been made under the provisions of`
  line `the Conservation of Foreign Exchange and Prevention of Smuggling Activities Act, 1974 (52 of`
  line `1974) on or before the filing of declaration:`
  line
  line `Provided that--`
  line
  line `(i) such order of detention, being an order to which the provisions of section 9 or section 12A`
  line `of the said Act do not apply, has not been revoked on the report of the Advisory Board under`
  line `section 8 of the said Act or before the receipt of the report of the Advisory Board; or`
  line
  line `(ii) such order of detention, being an order to which the provisions of section 9 of the said Act`
  line `apply, has not been revoked before the expiry of the time for, or on the basis of, the review under`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 9, or on the report of the Advisory Board under section 8, read with`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 9, of the said Act; or`
  line
  line `(iii) such order of detention, being an order to which the provisions of section 12A of the said`
  line `Act apply, has not been revoked before the expiry of the time for, or on the basis of, the first`
  line `review under sub-section (3) of that section, or on the basis of the report of the Advisory Board`
  line `under section 8, read with sub-section (6) of section 12A, of the said Act; or`
  line
  line `(iv) such order of detention has not been set aside by a court of competent jurisdiction;`
  line
  line `(c) to any person in respect of whom prosecution for any offence punishable under the provisions`
  line `of the Unlawful Activities (Prevention) Act, 1967 (37 of 1967), the Narcotic Drugs and Psychotropic`
  line `Substances Act, 1985 (61 of 1985), the Prevention of Corruption Act, 1988 (49 of 1988), the`
  line `Prevention of Money Laundering Act, 2002 (15 of 2003), the Prohibition of Benami Property`
  line `Transactions Act, 1988 (45 of 1988) has been instituted on or before the filing of the declaration or`
  line `such person has been convicted of any such offence punishable under any of those Acts;`
  line
  line `(d) to any person in respect of whom prosecution has been initiated by an Income-tax authority`
  line `for any offence punishable under the provisions of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860) or for the`
  line `purpose of enforcement of any civil liability under any law for the time being in force, on or before`
  line `the filing of the declaration or such person has been convicted of any such offence consequent to the`
  line `prosecution initiated by an Income tax authority;`
  line
  line `(e) to any person notified under section 3 of the Special Court (Trial of Offences Relating to`
  line `Transactions in Securities) Act, 1992 (27 of 1992) on or before the filing of declaration.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (49841)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Power of Board to issue directions, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00039_202003_1584597766943&sectionId=49841&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00039_202003_1584597766943
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Board of Direct Taxes may, from time`
  line `to time, issue such directions or orders to the income-tax authorities, as it may deem fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that no direction or order shall be issued so as to require any designated authority to dispose`
  line `of a particular case in a particular manner.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, the said Board may, if it considers`
  line `necessary or expedient so to do, for the purpose of this Act, including collection of revenue, issue from`
  line `time to time, general or special orders in respect of any class of cases, setting forth directions or`
  line `instructions as to the guidelines, principles or procedures to be followed by the authorities in any work`
  line `relating to this Act, including collection of revenue and issue such order, if the Board is of the opinion`
  line `that it is necessary in the public interest so to do.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (49842)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Power to remove difficulties`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00039_202003_1584597766943&sectionId=49842&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00039_202003_1584597766943
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may, by order, not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, remove`
  line `the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made after the expiry of a period of two years from the date on`
  line `which the provisions of this Act come into force.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under sub-section (1) shall, as soon as may be after it is made, be laid before`
  line `each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (49843)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00039_202003_1584597766943&sectionId=49843&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00039_202003_1584597766943
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules for carrying out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may provide for all or any`
  line `of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the form in which a declaration may be made, and the manner of its verification under`
  line `section 4;`
  line
  line `(b) the form and manner in which declarant shall furnish undertaking under sub-section (5) of`
  line `section 4;`
  line
  line `(c) the form in which certificate shall be granted under sub-section (1) of section 5;`
  line
  line `(d) the form in which payment shall be intimated under sub-section (2) of section 5;`
  line
  line `(e) determination of disputed tax including the manner of set-off in respect of brought forward or`
  line `carry forward of tax credit under section 115JAA or section 115JD of the Income-tax Act or set-off in`
  line `respect of brought forward or carry forward of loss or allowance of depreciation under the provisions`
  line `of the Income-tax Act;`
  line
  line `(f) the manner of calculating the amount payable under this Act;`
  line
  line `(g) any other matter which is to be, or may be, prescribed, or in respect of which provision is to`
  line `be made, by rules.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made by the Central Government under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it`
  line `is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days, which`
  line `may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the`
  line `session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in`
  line `making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that`
  line `any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
